    <p>In a year when the NYPD's suicide rate has already reached twice its anual average, police officers should also be addressing this issue. According to one 2018 study by the Ruderman Family, more law enforcement officers die by suicide than in the line of duty, and estimates that 90 percent of police officers who die by suicide use a firearm.  </p>

